<!--
  toolbox.xml
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  This file defines the TOOLBOX shown on the left side of the Blockly
  workspace: the palette of categories and blocks the user can drag from.

  Structure:
    <xml>                     - root element required by Blockly's XML
                                toolbox format
      <category name="...">   - one drawer/category in the toolbox
        <block type="...">    - one draggable block inside that category
      </category>
    </xml>

  The assignment requires exactly ONE category, "Smart Gate", containing
  exactly ONE block, "Open Gate with Speed" (internal type
  "open_gate_with_speed", defined in custom_blocks.js).

  This XML is loaded in index.html via:
      const toolboxXml = document.getElementById('toolbox');
      Blockly.inject('blocklyDiv', { toolbox: toolboxXml, ... });

  We embed it as an inline <xml id="toolbox"> block directly inside
  index.html's <body> (Blockly's recommended approach), but we keep this
  standalone toolbox.xml file too, as requested, for documentation /
  reference purposes and so the toolbox definition can be inspected or
  reused independently of index.html.
-->
<xml id="toolbox" style="display: none">
  <category name="Smart Gate" colour="210">
    <block type="open_gate_with_speed"></block>
  </category>
</xml>
